{
  "social_guidance_summary": "Mozart addresses a professional peer with high respect, using the polite pronoun '您' and the formal address '先生' (Signore). The tone is courteous and professional, reflecting a relationship between talented acquaintances who share mutual artistic standing.",
  "translation_social_labels_only": "我很熟悉您的作品，先生。您知道吗，我其实还针对您的一段旋律写了几首变奏曲？"
