{
  "social_guidance_summary": "Commodus exercises his imperial authority by issuing a harsh, direct command to subordinates. As the speaker holds absolute power, the tone is imperative and cold, with no need for politeness. The register reflects a ruler's callousness toward both the subjects and the object of the command.",
  "translation_social_labels_only": "把它扔到街上去！扔进广场！既然他们想要我父皇，那就把他交给他们！"
