  "translation_social_labels_only": "既然我们已经彻底告别了那种迷恋。"
}

{
  "social_guidance_summary": "As the master and manager, Proximo uses a commanding yet persuasive tone to negotiate with his gladiator. He employs a direct, informal register suitable for their transactional relationship, emphasizing the financial reward and the physical danger to Narcissus to ensure he follows the plan.",
  "translation_social_labels_only": "但你非上场不可！我会多分你一些，不止那三分之一！等我拿到钱……你只管假死倒地！你伤得太重没法真打，而那家伙可是个杀人狂！"
}

{
  "social_guidance_summary": "Narcissus speaks to Proximo with the cynical familiarity of a star gladiator who understands his own market value. Despite their formal enslaver-enslaved relationship, the local power dynamic is balanced by Proximo's desperation, resulting in a conversational, informal tone that is slightly mocking yet business-minded.",
  "translation_social_labels_only": "压力很大吧，普罗希摩？这事儿油水肯定不少。不然，你哪舍得把我这么个抢手货给踢出门？"
}

{
  "social_guidance_summary": "Proximo, as the master/manager, holds higher power and uses a direct, authoritative tone to dismiss Narcissus's skepticism. While the relationship is enslaver-enslaved, the tone is neutrally respectful, focusing on a persuasive yet firm command to ensure compliance with the business arrangement.",
  "translation_social_labels_only": "绝不是那回事！这是为了你好！快点，把剩下的盔甲都穿上！"
}

{
